When using a useEffect double check that we need if, it the useEffect is using lots of useState calls in it like this:

  useEffect(() => {
    if (document) {
      setDocumentName(document.name || '')
      setDescription(document.description || '')
      setMustBeRead(document.mustBeRead || false)
      setExpiry(document.expiry || '')
    }
  }, [document])

  We should probably just use a dirved state pattern and remove the useEffect altogether. 

  Always double check that the UseEffect is indeed actaully required. 
